Definition: a severe form of muscular dystrophy marked by generalized weakness and muscular wasting that affects the face and feet and hands and neck
Example: difficult speech and difficulty with the hands that spreads to the arms and shoulders and legs and hips; the onset can be any time from birth to middle age and the progression is slow; inheritance is autosomal dominant
Synonyms: myotonic_dystrophy, myotonia_atrophica, Steinert, s_disease, muscular_dystrophy, a, severe, form, of, muscular, dystrophy, marked, by, generalized, weakness, and, wasting, that, affects, the, face, feet, hands, neck, difficult, speech, difficulty, with, spreads, to, arms, shoulders, legs, hips, onset, can, be, any, time, from, birth, middle, age, progression, is, slow, inheritance, autosomal, dominant
Category: noun.state
